annotationA: Small ribonucleoprotein particle protein SmD2 (SmD2) is an RNA binding protein that forms a heterodimeric sub-complex with SmD1. They function as part of the heteroheptameric ring complex Sm core, which is involved in the formation of spliceosomal small nuclear RNPs (U1, U2, U4 and U5), which together catalyze pre-mRNA splicing
annotationB: RNA-binding protein 1; Contributes to the activation of female-specific DSX splicing in vivo by recognizing the RBP1 target sequences within the purine-rich polypyrimidine tract of the female-specific 3' splice site; Belongs to the splicing factor SR family
